    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-04-14T14:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1960-04-14T14:15:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <head>312. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d312fn0"
                        >Source: Department of State, Secretary’s Memoranda of Conversation: Lot 64
                        D 199. Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CDR1"
                            >Carlson</persName> and approved in M on April 22 and in <gloss
                            target="#t_S1">S</gloss> on April 25. The meeting was held in Secretary
                            <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName>’s office. See also <ref
                            target="#d311">Documents 311</ref> and <ref target="#d313"
                            >313</ref>–<ref target="#d315">315</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">US/<gloss target="#t_MC1">MC</gloss>/43</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1960-04-14T14:15:00">April 14, 1960, 2:15 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">FOREIGN MINISTERS MEETING</p>
                <p rend="center">Washington, April 12–14, 1960</p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Bomarc Program</item>
                </list>
                <p>[Here follows the same list of participants as <ref target="#d311">Document
                        311</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GHC1">Green</persName> inquired how significant the
                    successful test flight of the Bomarc? in Florida on April 13 had been. He
                    mentioned that Bomarc had become a “whipping boy” in Canada and that criticism
                    was being <pb facs="0827" n="791" xml:id="pg_791"/> generated with each failure
                    of a test. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> thought the
                    successful flight of the Bomarc was very significant. He added, however, that
                    Senator <persName>Chavez</persName> had made some remarks about the Bomarc which
                    would not be helpful in Canada. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_GHC1">Green</persName>
                    asked what these remarks were and was informed that the Senator had said in
                    effect that the United States was trying to impose on the poor Canadians a
                    missile that is so bad we cannot use it.</p>
            </div>
